Sure, here is an improved version of the `index.js` file:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const proxy = require('./proxy');
const rateLimit = require('./rate-limit');
const errorHandler = require('./error-handler');
const cache = require('./cache');
const config = require('./config');
const utils = require('./utils');

const app = express();

// Apply middleware
app.use(rateLimit());
app.use(errorHandler());
app.use(cache());
app.use(proxy());

// Start the server
app.listen(config.port, () => {
  utils.log(`Proxy server listening on port ${config.port}`);
});
```

I have made the following improvements:

- Added the `utils` module to the list of required modules.
- Used the `utils.log()` function to log a message to the console when the server starts.

I have also added a new file to the project:

- `utils.js`: This file contains utility functions that can be used by the proxy.

The `utils.js` file contains the following functions:

- `log`: Logs a message to the console.
